<br>
They sent a shipment of MOD recycled fuel to Korea or some country, and the safety records had been falsified, so they had to be returned (on a 6 week trip) back to England. Greenpeace have boats in the Irish Sea on a massive protest, and the shipment returning to Stellafield had to be protected by Irish/British navy/army while in their sea's which also costs loads. The main concern of course is a terrorist attack against the ship.<br>
<br>
PS - this was the headlines last week in the UK.. <p></p><span class=m><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uconfound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoNfOuNd</A> at: 9/21/02 2:38:59 am<br></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/udashofmooo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dash Of Mooo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/Strobe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/lene1c.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Moooo!!<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-vip.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 9/21/02 9:52:29 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Shut Down Stellafield</span><hr size=1> Umm.. its Sellafield. lol<br>
<br>
Firstly I actually agree with the government policies of the mid 60's to late 1970's that there should be alternatives to fossil fuels, particularly oil. They recognised that oil was a finite resource and that the primary source of the oil - the middle east - was unstable &amp; OPEC was well underway. In addition to North Sea exploration(or exploitation) they also began to build nuclear power stations.<br>
<br>
As far as I'm aware - I'm not that well read on Sellafield - this station was set up primarily as a means of processing the spent fuel from the other reactors around the UK. In fairness then - it's perhaps no surprise that it's costing money to run.<br>
<br>
I think now the days of nuclear fuel are over, and that there are much better alternatives to oil, which are safer. I also firmly believe that Greenpeace and the other pressure groups are misunderstanding this whole issue. Nuclear waste processing is big business - but its also very neccesary. Protesting against the reprocessing of this waste doesn't really make sense. In fact I'd rather have the stuff processed here because I believe its safer. Okay the recent case was unfortunate - but thats how these sensitive issues go. I'd rather have a well protected ship, then a very very big environmental disaster.<br>
<br>
So what should happen? Well I'm afraid I think nothing. The UK needs a reprocessing facility and with the closure of Torness(near Wick, North coast of Scotland) the only viable plant is Sellafield. I'm aware of the environmental concerns but I'm quietly(perhaps foolishly)trusting that these issues are now sorted. It's surely not making a mess of the Irish sea anymore?<br>
<br>
Perhaps we need a public investigation, but guess what, that will cost millions too.  <br>
<br>
You can't change the past, only influence the future. Sign petitions for green fuels instead.<br>
<br>
Good topic. My apologies for taking so long to respond.<br>
<br>
Dash <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uconfound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoNfOuNd</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://peter.armo.co.uk/img/irish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Createur de Projets<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-admin.gif' /><br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-vip.gif' /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 9/21/02 9:09:43 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Shut Down Stellafield</span><hr size=1> The Irish government had an investigation into Sellafield, or Stellafield as I keep on calling it. They found out it was affecting people that live within a few hundred miles of it, and they want it shut down. They lodged a legal case in the European High Court yet I don't know the results of it. It's probably in waiting for several years...<br>
<br>
Then again, the Scottish government found out that all the landfill sites in N Ireland where affecting the islands and the eastern coast of Scotland, but the government have launched big recycling schemes and advertising ventures against landfill. Actually, I am one of the few hundred people in N Ireland that is testing a compost machine. They plan to launch this across the country next year, giving every house their own compost machine for free if they want one. They are doing research over the next year to see whether it's worth it.<br>
<br>
As for Sellafield, I believe it does affect the people that live around it - for hundreds of miles. I don't know how it will affect us in the future, but I believe it is affecting us now in very minor ways. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 bgcolor=#FFFFFF><table cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td align=right class=headings> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"></a>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"></a>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.emailToFriend?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/email.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="email this topic to a friend"></a> </td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td valign="top"></td><td align=right valign="top"><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/ezb/ez-topic.jpg border=0 alt="New Topic"></a>  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/ezb/ez-reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a>  </td></tr><tr><td valign="top"></td><td align=right valign="top"><form action=http://pub9